lyrics:
I was drowning in the dark
Couldn't see the light
My lungs were giving up
I had no will to fight
But then you came along
And pulled me from the deep
You taught me how to breathe
You gave me hope to keep

You're my pulmonary therapist
You make me feel alive
You're my pulmonary therapist
You help me to survive
You're the rhythm of my heart
You're the treadmill of my life
You're my pulmonary therapist
You're the reason why I strive

You put me on a path
To heal and to grow
You pushed me to the limit
But you never let me go
You showed me how to live
And not to be afraid
You taught me how to breathe
You made me unafraid

You're my pulmonary therapist
You make me feel alive
You're my pulmonary therapist
You help me to survive
Thank you
style: cheerful music for children music piano
